The paper discusses the use of robots (cobots) in human-populated environments and their ability to autonomously construct plans. This suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the importance of making these plans understandable and predictable for humans, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of conditional random fields (CRFs) for learning the labeling scheme of humans suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper's focus on constructing plans that do not surprise humans suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY).
